  "text": "• Arthritis: The involvement of the cervical spine is the most serious skeletal manifestation of rheumatoid arthritis. In patients with basilar impression and/or rheumatoid cervical myelopathy, paresthesia in the upper limbs was significantly more common [CITATION_1] 138) . Paresthesia can occur in psoriatic arthritis [CITATION_2] .",
